 excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `msisensor_merge`\n\n# Real R-task: msisensor_merge\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `snakemake-workflows-msisensor-pro-finish` (family: `variant`, stage: `late`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given multiple MSIsensor outputs at\n`results/msi/<sample>/msi_out.txt` (tab-separated with header:\n`Total_Number_of_Sites, Number_of_Unstable_Sites, %`). Read all of them, tag\neach row with a `group` column extracted from the path (second path component\nafter `results/`), rename `Total_Number_of_Sites -> n_all_sites`,\n`Number_of_Unstable_Sites -> n_unstable_sites`, `% -> msi_score`, and write\nto `output/merged_msi.tsv` via `readr::write_tsv`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/merged_msi.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: merged_msi.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {},\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {},\n  \"results\": {\n    \"msi\": {\n      \"caseA\": {\n        \"msi_out.txt\": {\n          \"_file\": \"msi_out.txt\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"caseB\": {\n        \"msi_out.txt\": {\n          \"_file\": \"msi_out.txt\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"caseC\": {\n        \"msi_out.txt\": {\n          \"_file\": \"msi_out.txt\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/merged_msi.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_JxfC5HMUWInHdwbwhgN3svWX", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. List all files in the `results/msi` directory to identify the MSIsensor output files.\\n2. Read each `msi_out.txt` file, extract the sample identifier from the file path, and rename the columns as specified.\\n3. Merge all the processed data into a single data frame.\\n4. Write the merged data frame to `output/merged_msi.tsv` using `readr::write_tsv`.\\n5. Verify the existence of `output/merged_msi.tsv` and submit the task as done if successful.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (444 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_JxfC5HMUWInHdwbwhgN3svWX"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_3MTESYNMz6JKCtUtrWASQwcH", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(dplyr)\\nlibrary(readr)\\nlibrary(purrr)\\n\\n# Define the file path pattern\\nfile_paths <- list.files(path = \\\"results/msi\\\", pattern = \\\"msi_out.txt\\\", recursive = TRUE, full.names = TRUE)\\n\\n# Function to read and process each file\\nprocess_file <- function(file_path) {\\n  sample_id <- strsplit(file_path, \\\"/\\\")[[1]][3]\\n  read_tsv(file_path) %>%\\n    mutate(group = sample_id) %>%\\n    rename(n_all_sites = Total_Number_of_Sites,\\n           n_unstable_sites = Number_of_Unstable_Sites,\\n           msi_score = `%`)\\n}\\n\\n# Read, process, and combine all files\\nmerged_data <- map_dfr(file_paths, process_file)\\n\\n# Write the combined data to a TSV file\\nwrite_tsv(merged_data, \\\"output/merged_msi.tsv\\\")\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=0\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\nRows: 1 Columns: 3\n\u2500\u2500 Column specification \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nDelimiter: \"\\t\"\ndbl (3): Total_Number_of_Sites, Number_of_Unstable_Sites, %\n\n\u2139 Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.\n\u2139 Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.\nRows: 1 Columns: 3\n\u2500\u2500 Column specification \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\